snippet.textDisplay: So I'm bouncing around the 'YouTubes' looking a car-motorcycle-aircraft repair-restorations-welding etc. Then I run across your title, "LED Lights Makeup Challenge" and immediately know that the end results are going to be... "Your mileage may vary". So I begin to watch BUT, I just had to skip through to see the end results. YUP! Just as you and I expected. The result made you look like a Kabuki dancer in a drag show. At first it's hilarious then it becomes a fantastic study of how important light plays in our daily lives and how it affects the other colors with it. I think this is a brilliant public challenge and also that you can laugh at yourself made me smile. Thanks for entertaining us during these trying times.

snippet.textDisplay:
Red shades would seem lighter as it matches the redness of the light. It "cancels out" the shade making it white. Think old-school 3D sunglasses. Red lines seem white (invisible) under the red lens so you only see the blue ones and the same happens on the blue lens side with the blue lines.

But this was so much fun!!!!
